## Contributing

Contributions are welcome. Please open an issue or PR on [GitHub](https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/leakfix).

### How to contribute

1. Fork the repository and clone locally.
2. Open an issue to discuss proposed changes.
3. Submit a pull request with a clear description of changes.

### Development setup

```bash
# Clone and enter the repo
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/leakfix.git && cd leakfix

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # or .venv\Scripts\activate on Windows

# Install in editable mode with dependencies
pip install -e .
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install external tools (required for full functionality)
brew install gitleaks git-filter-repo

# Run tests (requires pytest)
pip install pytest
python -m pytest
```

Run `leakfix --help` to verify the CLI is available.

